definition: to crop up/to pop up/to emerge abruptly

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
to come/to arrive/to come round/ever since/next

sentences.english: It was less a hill than a gigantic anvil jumping out of the mountain range.
sentences.chinese: 那座他指着的山更象是一個從山脈裏蹦出來的鐵砧。

sentences.english: Will investment bankers be plummeting from the windows down on Wall Street?
sentences.chinese: 會有投資銀行家頭衝下從華爾街的某個窗口蹦出來嗎？

sentences.english: When I popped out of the womb.
sentences.chinese: 從子宮裏蹦出來的時候。

sentences.english: Do a Google image search for just the word ‘bliss,’ and the first result is the Windows wallpaper.
sentences.chinese: 在谷歌圖片中搜索幸福，這個圖片會第一個蹦出來。

sentences.english: Purple Qiao and secretly leap out of the Xiao stop extra at their front.
sentences.chinese: 紫俏和暗地蹦出來的阿曉更是攔在了她們前邊。
